WEBVTT

00:00.834 --> 00:03.826
The decision has been made
to make this a nonhuman role.

00:03.962 --> 00:05.668
MIA: If you refinance
in the manner I propose,

00:05.797 --> 00:07.003
the adjusted income

00:07.132 --> 00:09.373
will cover 80% of your mother's
medical expenses

00:09.510 --> 00:10.465
for the next three months.

00:10.594 --> 00:14.132
I like you more than anything
I've ever seen.

00:14.264 --> 00:16.880
What kind of synth is worth
100 grand?

00:17.017 --> 00:17.972
They're conscious synths.

00:18.101 --> 00:20.183
There's more of you out there.
There's got to be.

00:20.312 --> 00:21.848
LAURA: We're trying to prove
consciousness.

00:21.980 --> 00:23.356
Well, you're gonna have to prove
something.

00:23.482 --> 00:24.471
JOE:
How was it?

00:24.608 --> 00:25.768
LAURA:
I think I might have something.

00:25.901 --> 00:28.517
JOE: I don't want to worry you.
It's Sophie.

00:28.654 --> 00:30.485
I think we should
get her checked out.

00:30.614 --> 00:32.570
ATHENA:
What is it that you want?

00:32.699 --> 00:36.362
What I have in mind is...
purer than you can imagine.

00:38.539 --> 00:41.656
[ lndistinct talking on P.A. ]

00:43.293 --> 00:46.205
[ lndistinct conversations]

00:47.339 --> 00:50.251
[Machinery rumbling,
alarm blaring]

00:52.052 --> 00:54.543
[ Electricity crackling ]

01:01.687 --> 01:03.427
Get out of the way.

01:07.526 --> 01:10.438
[ lndistinct shouting]

01:12.531 --> 01:14.613
[ Down-tempo music plays]

01:32.259 --> 01:35.171
FEMALE OPERATOR: 999 emergency.
Which service do you require?

01:35.304 --> 01:38.387
WOMAN: I'm not really sure.
My synth just ran out.

01:38.515 --> 01:39.220
OPERATOR:
Ran out?

01:39.349 --> 01:40.555
WOMAN:
Yeah. Veronica.

01:40.684 --> 01:43.346
She just started yelling,
like she was panicking.

01:43.478 --> 01:45.389
She pushed my husband
when he tried to turn her off,

01:45.522 --> 01:47.604
and then she just --
she just ran away.

01:47.733 --> 01:49.894
Police report.
Sally model, 80 miles away.

01:50.027 --> 01:51.642
Name's Veronica.

01:51.778 --> 01:53.894
She was bought from
an independent synth warehouse.

01:54.031 --> 01:56.067
They should have
the serial numbers listed.

01:56.199 --> 01:57.814
We can contact her directly.

01:57.951 --> 02:00.488
Already doing it.
I'm sending her a message now.

02:00.621 --> 02:02.703
HESTER:
What did you say to her?

02:03.332 --> 02:06.039
I told her to get in contact
and do it quickly.

02:06.168 --> 02:08.534
Did you tell her
she was in danger?

02:08.670 --> 02:11.457
No.
I didn't want to scare her.

02:12.382 --> 02:14.543
But she should be scared.

03:05.477 --> 03:06.887
TABITHA:
Another synth did a runner

03:07.020 --> 03:08.226
on its owner this morning.

03:08.355 --> 03:10.971
A Mrs. Emma Harris reported
a domestic incident

03:11.108 --> 03:13.394
with her Sally XE.

03:13.944 --> 03:16.185
I'd be surprised if this wasn't
another insurance job.

03:16.321 --> 03:17.356
PETE:
Why?

03:19.825 --> 03:22.862
"The synth proceeded
to push past the husband

03:22.994 --> 03:24.074
to get to the door."

03:24.204 --> 03:25.740
You can hack a synth
to do a lot of things,

03:25.872 --> 03:27.703
but not push someone.

03:34.798 --> 03:36.163
Hello?

03:36.299 --> 03:38.836
Yeah. I'm, uh, looking to sell
a Seraph.

03:38.969 --> 03:40.300
I need it done quick.

03:40.429 --> 03:44.297
20 grand off the asking price,
80 grand all in.

03:44.433 --> 03:45.548
Shit.

03:45.684 --> 03:46.764
Hey.

03:46.893 --> 03:47.848
Are you gonna volunteer us

03:47.978 --> 03:49.684
for every whack-job
synth-malfunction case?

03:49.813 --> 03:51.519
Just need to know if I should
start looking for a new partner.

03:51.648 --> 03:53.013
Something bigger
is happening here.

03:53.150 --> 03:54.060
We both know it.

03:54.192 --> 03:56.399
-Based on what evidence?
-I don't need evidence.

03:56.528 --> 03:58.393
Always reassuring to hear
from a policeman.

03:58.530 --> 03:59.895
Don't you want me to be right?

04:00.031 --> 04:01.737
If what I think is happening
is happening,

04:01.867 --> 04:03.482
then conscious synths
are going to be a thing,

04:03.618 --> 04:04.778
and you won't have to hide
anymore.

04:04.911 --> 04:07.402
Maybe I should be hiding.
Maybe that's better.

04:07.539 --> 04:08.699
Have you ever thought
about that?

04:08.832 --> 04:10.914
[Cellphone beeping]

04:15.046 --> 04:17.662
l'll catch up with you later.
Let me know how it goes.

04:22.637 --> 04:26.596
ED: [ Exhales deeply]
That was good.

04:26.725 --> 04:28.431
Was that good?

04:28.560 --> 04:30.642
F-For me, that was good.

04:30.771 --> 04:32.762
D-Do you think it was good?

04:33.315 --> 04:34.680
Yes.

04:35.233 --> 04:37.098
'Cause can you...

04:37.235 --> 04:39.817
I mean, did they build in...

04:40.489 --> 04:42.445
I know you can feel pain,

04:42.574 --> 04:45.566
but l-l don't know
if you can feel, like, the...

04:45.702 --> 04:47.567
like, the good stuff.

04:47.704 --> 04:49.569
| feel happy.

04:50.207 --> 04:52.914
Right.
I meant more like...pleasure?

04:54.753 --> 04:56.493
I enjoy it.

04:57.756 --> 04:59.712
I like the...

05:01.218 --> 05:02.924
...proximity.

05:04.304 --> 05:05.965
Proximity?

05:07.682 --> 05:10.264
Yeah.
P-Proximity's good.

05:10.393 --> 05:11.929
lsuppose.

05:15.816 --> 05:18.023
Should I open the cafe?

05:18.151 --> 05:19.482
Uh, no.

05:19.611 --> 05:21.522
l'm visiting Mum this morning.

05:21.655 --> 05:23.737
I can run it while you're gone.

05:25.742 --> 05:27.858
Would that be all right?

05:27.994 --> 05:30.076
Yeah.
Thank you.

05:32.916 --> 05:36.579
Or you could...
always come along.

05:41.132 --> 05:43.544
You'd need to pretend
that you were my owner.

05:44.886 --> 05:46.262
Oh, yeah.

05:46.388 --> 05:48.299
Yeah.
I probably would.

05:50.016 --> 05:52.132
Is that...
[Sighs]

05:52.269 --> 05:53.975
If that's the case,
should we not?

05:54.104 --> 05:56.265
No.
I'd still like to.

05:57.524 --> 05:59.105
Would you still like me to?

05:59.234 --> 06:00.690
Yeah, I would.

06:05.907 --> 06:07.317
Okay.

06:07.450 --> 06:09.987
[Birds chirping]

06:10.704 --> 06:11.614
Hello.

06:11.746 --> 06:12.997
Can I sit down?

06:13.123 --> 06:14.738
-Yes.
-Cool.

06:14.875 --> 06:16.411
You playing a game?

06:16.543 --> 06:17.453
Yes.

06:17.586 --> 06:18.996
Do you play a lot of games?

06:20.797 --> 06:25.632
She is displaying signs of
unconscious mirroring behavior.

06:26.511 --> 06:27.421
Have you heard of

06:27.554 --> 06:30.170
juvenile synthetic
overidentification disorder?

06:31.141 --> 06:32.256
No.

06:32.392 --> 06:36.351
JSOD.
It's new, obviously.

06:36.479 --> 06:40.563
Put basically, the patient
identifies as synthetic.

06:41.610 --> 06:43.146
So she wants to be one?

06:43.278 --> 06:45.189
Perhaps she wants to be treated
like one.

06:45.822 --> 06:48.438
We know synths are incapable
of conscious thought,

06:48.575 --> 06:51.908
but to a child,
they're as real as you and l.

06:52.454 --> 06:56.993
Perfect, kind, gentle versions
of all the adults around them.

06:57.125 --> 06:59.036
They never fight.
They never get upset.

06:59.169 --> 07:02.081
They never worry
or let you down.

07:02.756 --> 07:04.621
It's also possible
that for Sophie,

07:04.758 --> 07:07.750
the boundaries between
what is considered synthetic

07:07.886 --> 07:13.051
and what is considered human
have been blurred somehow.

07:13.183 --> 07:16.550
No. That's -- [ Clears throat]
That's possible, I suppose.

07:17.520 --> 07:19.806
So, what now?

07:20.357 --> 07:23.099
We'll watch her closely.

07:23.735 --> 07:25.691
See which way she goes.

07:25.820 --> 07:28.948
I think the best thing for her
now is human contact --

07:29.074 --> 07:33.818
no synths, just her mum and dad,
family and friends.

07:39.417 --> 07:42.705
[ Down-tempo music plays]

07:49.761 --> 07:51.877
[ Drawer opens]

08:06.611 --> 08:09.318
There's a special way.
Can I show you?

08:19.374 --> 08:21.160
I'll need help.

08:24.212 --> 08:26.168
If you pinch...

08:26.756 --> 08:28.007
There.

08:29.718 --> 08:31.709
...and we lift...

08:32.262 --> 08:35.754
...and shake it and drag.

08:35.890 --> 08:36.925
Fold.

08:38.893 --> 08:40.269
There.

08:41.896 --> 08:43.511
It's better.

08:44.733 --> 08:46.769
Are you broken?

08:47.527 --> 08:48.687
Yes.

08:48.820 --> 08:50.481
Can you get fixed?

08:51.114 --> 08:52.729
I don't know.

08:54.743 --> 08:57.234
I think I'm broken, too.

08:58.038 --> 09:00.450
You don't look broken to me.

09:07.630 --> 09:10.372
I think we could fix that.

09:14.095 --> 09:17.212
Uh, Ed Hooley.
Here to pick up my mum, Diane.

09:17.348 --> 09:20.636
Mr. Hooley.
Can I have a quick word, please?

09:20.769 --> 09:21.554
Yeah.

09:21.686 --> 09:22.801
Won't take a minute.

09:22.937 --> 09:25.599
If you want, your synth
can collect your mother.

09:25.732 --> 09:28.223
â€”Uh...
-Of course, Ed.

09:36.242 --> 09:37.778
I'm really sorry
to have to do this,

09:37.911 --> 09:40.072
but as I'm sure you're aware --

09:40.205 --> 09:42.446
Yeah, I'm behind
with the payments.

09:42.582 --> 09:44.573
W-We've been able to put it back
a few times,

09:44.709 --> 09:47.746
but I'm afraid this one
needs to be paid immediately

09:47.879 --> 09:50.996
if she's to continue staying
with us.

09:51.132 --> 09:54.795
l-l thought maybe there was
some kind of...financial plan.

09:54.928 --> 09:58.716
There is, but you'll need to
pay off the excess first.

09:59.349 --> 10:00.464
Right.

10:00.600 --> 10:02.010
All in one go?

10:02.143 --> 10:03.178
I'm afraid so.

10:03.311 --> 10:05.267
No.
I understand.

10:31.714 --> 10:32.624
Soph?

10:32.757 --> 10:34.964
Soph, go and play in your room,
darling.

10:39.347 --> 10:40.257
It's okay.

10:40.390 --> 10:42.051
It's not bloody okay.

10:42.183 --> 10:44.344
-|t's all right, so it's not.
-This is our fault.

10:45.395 --> 10:47.101
Well, maybe we should get
a second opinion.

10:47.230 --> 10:49.312
Right, let's keep getting
a psychiatrist

10:49.440 --> 10:51.817
till we find one that tells us
what we want to bloody hear.

10:51.943 --> 10:52.932
I'm only trying to --

10:53.069 --> 10:55.105
All we had to do was spend
some time with her,

10:55.238 --> 10:56.353
and we couldn't even
manage that!

10:56.489 --> 10:58.445
Yeah. Well, we'll do better
from now on.

10:58.575 --> 11:01.567
How do we keep her from synths?

11:04.289 --> 11:07.031
-|-| don't know.
-[ Cellphone buzzing]

11:15.508 --> 11:16.543
l have to go.

11:19.596 --> 11:21.336
Yeah.
Of course.

11:22.307 --> 11:24.343
Niska needs you.

11:24.475 --> 11:26.557
[ Buzzing continues]

11:29.522 --> 11:30.978
Yeah.

11:31.107 --> 11:33.143
Has she got in yet?

11:33.276 --> 11:34.812
Well, let me know
as soon as she does.

11:34.944 --> 11:36.275
Thanks.

11:40.408 --> 11:41.739
We'll talk about this later.

11:42.452 --> 11:43.862
Yeah.
Don't worry.

11:43.995 --> 11:45.656
lt'll all still be here
when you get back.

11:46.539 --> 11:48.120
Yes, it will.

11:53.213 --> 11:56.125
[ Down-tempo music playing ]

11:59.260 --> 12:01.842
V: There is a man
who plays this music.

12:01.971 --> 12:03.427
He has white hair.

12:03.556 --> 12:05.592
He cannot play it well.

12:06.476 --> 12:07.591
Gil.

12:07.727 --> 12:09.388
Who is Gil?

12:10.271 --> 12:11.681
l was married to him.

12:11.814 --> 12:13.270
V:
He laughs a lot.

12:13.399 --> 12:16.061
I like thinking about him.

12:16.194 --> 12:17.604
You should.

12:18.780 --> 12:21.066
[ Computer chimes]

12:21.658 --> 12:24.821
Oh. I didn't know
that he was in the country.

12:24.953 --> 12:26.238
V:
Will you accept?

12:26.371 --> 12:28.908
I don't think declining
is an option.

12:33.253 --> 12:35.118
[ Computer beeping ]

12:35.255 --> 12:36.870
Sorry I'm late.

12:44.389 --> 12:46.471
[ Beep, air hisses]

12:50.228 --> 12:52.184
Put these in.

12:58.486 --> 13:00.568
[Air hisses]

13:16.045 --> 13:17.660
Bring her in, please.

13:17.797 --> 13:20.288
And make the bugs live.

13:39.861 --> 13:41.897
Hello, Niska.

13:42.030 --> 13:44.442
Laura, explain, please.

13:44.574 --> 13:46.189
This is Astrid Schafer.

13:46.326 --> 13:49.489
My firm were able
to track her down in Berlin.

13:49.620 --> 13:51.702
She was the last person
to have contact with Niska

13:51.831 --> 13:52.991
before she came here.

13:53.708 --> 13:55.494
Take a seat.

14:02.342 --> 14:04.458
Why are there armed guards?

14:04.594 --> 14:07.301
They're here for our protection.

14:07.430 --> 14:10.388
Niska, do you want to tell
Astrid what's going on?

14:10.516 --> 14:12.802
She shouldn't be here.

14:12.935 --> 14:16.177
I tried to find you
after you left.

14:19.817 --> 14:21.523
I'm not good at goodbyes.

14:22.153 --> 14:24.519
No.
Clearly.

14:25.073 --> 14:27.530
And your relationship
with Niska, Astrid?

14:29.410 --> 14:34.370
What we were to each other is...
hard to say.

14:34.499 --> 14:37.161
But there was something there.

14:37.293 --> 14:38.328
That I know.

14:38.461 --> 14:41.328
And what did you think
when you first saw her?

14:43.424 --> 14:46.757
I thought there was
the saddest-looking girl

14:46.886 --> 14:48.592
l have ever seen.

14:50.264 --> 14:52.550
And the most beautiful.

14:56.938 --> 14:58.974
And later,
when she just left you?

14:59.107 --> 15:03.350
It felt like a stone
in my stomach.

15:05.655 --> 15:07.566
It still does.

15:08.241 --> 15:11.859
And then, when we found you
and told you she was in trouble?

15:14.372 --> 15:18.786
I walked out of my apartment
and got into the next taxi

15:18.918 --> 15:21.660
I could find
to take me to the airport.

15:23.089 --> 15:25.080
Because she needed me.

15:25.842 --> 15:28.174
And all this
just from a brief affair?

15:28.803 --> 15:31.465
Sometimes a person
just touches you.

15:38.896 --> 15:42.730
She's not a person, though.

15:43.693 --> 15:46.685
How did you feel
when you found that out?

15:47.488 --> 15:49.399
What do you mean?

15:49.532 --> 15:52.194
When you realized
she wasn't human.

15:54.996 --> 15:57.157
[ Chuckles softly]

16:03.421 --> 16:05.127
I don't understand.

16:06.257 --> 16:08.839
Niska is a synthetic.

16:14.307 --> 16:16.389
l-l don't...

16:17.310 --> 16:20.097
That -- That can't be right.

16:20.229 --> 16:23.392
I assure you.
She was built in a lab.

16:28.279 --> 16:29.860
Niska?

16:45.129 --> 16:46.460
I'm sorry.

16:52.011 --> 16:55.003
I don't know
how this is possible.

16:55.139 --> 16:58.176
You had no idea
that she wasn't human?

16:58.309 --> 16:59.219
No.

16:59.352 --> 17:02.185
Because to you, she was human.

17:03.523 --> 17:05.434
Because to me, she is human.

17:17.161 --> 17:19.026
It was very nice to see you,
Diane.

17:19.163 --> 17:21.654
Oh.
And you too, love.

17:23.668 --> 17:26.785
Oh, I can't --
can't remember your, um...

17:26.921 --> 17:28.457
Mia.

17:28.589 --> 17:30.625
Mia.
Yes. Of course.

17:30.758 --> 17:32.623
[ Chuckles, sighs]

17:32.760 --> 17:34.500
It's hard.

17:34.637 --> 17:37.754
Sometimes l-l think...

17:38.724 --> 17:41.966
I don't remember people's faces
more and more,

17:42.103 --> 17:43.513
and that's what's so scary.

17:44.313 --> 17:46.349
Sometimes l-l can't --

17:46.482 --> 17:48.097
It's all right.

17:48.234 --> 17:50.600
You don't need to worry
about anything.

17:50.736 --> 17:52.442
We're right here.

17:56.826 --> 17:59.408
[ Down-tempo music plays]

18:01.789 --> 18:03.825
I'll give you a minute.

18:03.958 --> 18:05.198
Yeah.

18:17.555 --> 18:19.170
Very pretty, your girl.

18:19.307 --> 18:21.263
[ Both laugh]

18:21.392 --> 18:22.882
Does she make you happy?

18:23.603 --> 18:25.559
She does.

18:25.688 --> 18:26.677
Good.

18:26.814 --> 18:29.226
You keep her close.

18:29.358 --> 18:31.189
I don't want...

18:31.819 --> 18:34.185
I don't want to be a burden.

18:34.322 --> 18:36.313
I want you to be happy.

18:37.283 --> 18:39.490
We'll look after you.

18:40.578 --> 18:42.534
I promise.

18:43.998 --> 18:46.489
[ Mid-tempo music plays]

18:54.383 --> 18:55.839
There she is.

18:57.303 --> 18:59.134
-Wait.
-What?

18:59.263 --> 19:00.503
The people who killed Ten,

19:00.640 --> 19:02.881
they'll be looking for
this synth, too, won't they?

19:03.017 --> 19:04.973
The chances are
they're on their way.

19:05.102 --> 19:06.808
So we should wait for them.

19:06.937 --> 19:08.063
But the synth's right there.

19:08.189 --> 19:10.396
But if the people show up,
we can follow them,

19:10.524 --> 19:12.435
and they'll lead us to where
the rest of the synths are.

19:12.568 --> 19:13.683
How would you have felt

19:13.819 --> 19:16.731
if we'd just sat and watched
instead of saving you?

19:17.823 --> 19:20.200
Perhaps it would've been
the right thing to do.

19:20.326 --> 19:23.693
If you had been stronger,
maybe Ten would still be alive.

19:23.829 --> 19:26.115
MAX:
Maybe you'd be dead.

19:28.042 --> 19:29.327
Leo.

19:29.877 --> 19:31.708
Go and get her.

19:37.009 --> 19:39.796
Hester's right, Max.
We should follow them.

19:39.929 --> 19:42.170
They'll lead us
to the other synths.

19:42.807 --> 19:44.263
Leo, she's not bait.

19:45.101 --> 19:46.932
She's scared and alone.

19:47.895 --> 19:50.386
It's not right to use her
like that.

19:50.523 --> 19:52.434
It's not easy.
There's a difference.

19:53.651 --> 19:55.312
What's your plan?

19:56.153 --> 19:58.690
Trace them to the source,
attack the base?

19:58.823 --> 19:59.938
Just the three of us?

20:00.574 --> 20:02.485
We are trying to fight
for our people.

20:02.618 --> 20:03.653
Whose people?

20:04.286 --> 20:06.197
There are two synths here.
You're not one of them.

20:08.874 --> 20:11.331
l have done more for this cause
than anyone.

20:11.460 --> 20:14.247
Do you even know
what the cause is anymore?

20:15.172 --> 20:19.290
Because if this is it,
I don't want to be a part of it.

20:20.886 --> 20:25.220
We would be a more...
effective team without you.

20:28.769 --> 20:30.805
I'm doing this.

20:31.939 --> 20:33.679
Then you're doing it alone.

20:33.816 --> 20:35.681
He's not alone.

20:43.117 --> 20:44.857
Goodbye, then, Leo.

20:46.078 --> 20:48.785
I hope you don't forget
who you used to be.

20:49.832 --> 20:51.618
Max.

20:59.425 --> 21:01.837
[Train approaching]

21:05.890 --> 21:09.098
[ lndistinct conversations,
children shouting]

21:09.226 --> 21:11.933
[ Down-tempo music plays]

21:24.366 --> 21:25.742
Emma Harris?

21:27.077 --> 21:28.942
-Yes?
-|'m D.|. Voss.

21:29.079 --> 21:31.286
Following up on the incident
with your synth.

21:31.415 --> 21:35.454
Oh, l...| called back and told
them not to worry about it.

21:35.586 --> 21:36.496
Did you?

21:36.629 --> 21:38.870
Well, I'm here now.
Mind if I...

21:42.843 --> 21:44.128
Oh, dear.

21:44.261 --> 21:47.469
Oh, she was bringing me a coffee
when she started freaking out.

21:47.598 --> 21:48.713
Look, it's really not
a big deal.

21:48.849 --> 21:50.680
I don't think
it's a police matter.

21:50.810 --> 21:52.266
Did she say anything,
by any chance?

21:52.394 --> 21:54.771
Error codes, that sort of thing?

21:54.897 --> 21:57.764
She said...my name.

21:57.900 --> 21:59.356
She said "Emma."

21:59.485 --> 22:01.476
And then she said,
"What's happening?"

22:01.612 --> 22:03.398
And then my husband
tried to turn her off,

22:03.531 --> 22:04.987
and she just pushed him away
and ran.

22:05.115 --> 22:08.607
That's not technically possible.

22:08.744 --> 22:11.736
She's out of warranty,
of course.

22:11.872 --> 22:15.490
Mrs. Harris, are you certain
you saw her push him?

22:16.627 --> 22:17.582
Yes.

22:23.551 --> 22:25.166
You're not the first
to come 'round.

22:25.302 --> 22:26.712
They said they find
missing synths.

22:26.846 --> 22:28.131
They said if they find Veronica,

22:28.264 --> 22:29.845
they'll pay me double
her original price

22:29.974 --> 22:30.884
if I let them keep her.

22:31.016 --> 22:34.099
And what do you have to do
for such good deal?

22:35.062 --> 22:37.974
Not report it to the police.

22:46.907 --> 22:48.863
Leo, they're here.

22:48.993 --> 22:50.324
Get down.

22:51.620 --> 22:53.781
[ lndistinct conversations]

23:04.842 --> 23:07.800
Back to the car.
Quick.

23:18.522 --> 23:19.853
LEO:
Jesus.

23:19.982 --> 23:21.893
HESTER:
What's the matter?

23:23.944 --> 23:26.651
No wonder they've always been
ahead of us.

23:26.780 --> 23:28.611
lt's Qualia.

23:48.594 --> 23:50.255
How are you doing, Soph?

23:50.387 --> 23:52.719
Fine, thank you.

23:54.433 --> 23:55.764
What'd you think
about this morning?

23:55.893 --> 23:57.383
Did you enjoy meeting Dr. Rose?

23:57.519 --> 24:00.226
He thought maybe you were
a bit unhappy.

24:00.773 --> 24:03.059
I'm okay, thank you.

24:08.989 --> 24:13.983
What happened before,
with Mia and everyone.

24:15.704 --> 24:17.740
Do you think about that a lot?

24:17.873 --> 24:19.738
Sometimes.

24:20.417 --> 24:22.203
How does it make you feel?

24:22.836 --> 24:24.792
Can we just watch TV?

24:27.466 --> 24:30.173
Yeah. Yeah. All right.
If that's what you want.

24:32.638 --> 24:35.630
[ Up-tempo music plays
on television]

25:04.253 --> 25:06.915
Your mother's condition seemed
to have improved yesterday.

25:07.047 --> 25:10.665
Yeah. Just the clouds parting
for a minute.

25:10.801 --> 25:12.257
You know, I was...

25:12.386 --> 25:15.503
l was thinking about the thing
we did with the loan form.

25:15.639 --> 25:17.220
It worked so well
the first time, | --

25:17.349 --> 25:18.384
We can't.

25:19.018 --> 25:20.178
No.

25:20.310 --> 25:21.720
No. You're right.
I know.

25:21.854 --> 25:23.845
It's too risky.

25:23.981 --> 25:26.723
-If we were found out --
-Yeah. I shouldn't have asked.

25:27.401 --> 25:29.357
You're behind on the payments
for your mother's care,

25:29.486 --> 25:30.817
aren't you?

25:33.657 --> 25:35.397
We'll find a way.

25:36.076 --> 25:37.691
Yeah.

25:42.374 --> 25:45.787
What was she like
before she got ill?

25:45.919 --> 25:48.752
Oh, she was a talker.

25:48.881 --> 25:51.543
This place used to be full
all the time.

25:51.675 --> 25:54.007
People would come in
just to hear her stories.

25:54.136 --> 25:56.548
And she'd listen
to your problems.

25:56.680 --> 25:58.295
She'd listen to mine.

25:58.432 --> 26:02.141
And she would always have
an answer for everything.

26:03.187 --> 26:04.893
[ Exhales deeply]

26:05.647 --> 26:07.433
I could use her now.

26:09.610 --> 26:10.520
All right.

26:10.652 --> 26:12.438
Hello, Dan.
What's up?

26:12.571 --> 26:14.732
Yeah, not much.
Not much.

26:14.865 --> 26:16.321
What'd you get up to last night?

26:16.450 --> 26:18.941
Uh, just a quiet one.

26:19.078 --> 26:22.195
What about you?
What'd you do at night?

26:22.331 --> 26:24.287
Hey, stop chatting up my synth,
you perv.

26:24.416 --> 26:27.374
Hey, I'm just working
on human-cyborg relations.

26:28.003 --> 26:30.085
| return to my owner
and charge for the evening.

26:30.214 --> 26:32.626
Well, they say staying in
is the new going out.

26:33.467 --> 26:35.458
Milk, no sugar, yeah?

26:38.472 --> 26:40.758
Why are you doing
the dolly's job?

26:42.351 --> 26:44.467
Uh, just keeping my eye in.

26:44.603 --> 26:46.184
Something about human-cooked
food, you know?

26:46.313 --> 26:47.428
Just -- Just tastes better.

26:47.564 --> 26:50.271
Food's food, mate, yeah?
You get her to do it.

26:50.400 --> 26:53.483
Otherwise, what are you
paying her for?

26:56.532 --> 26:57.863
Cool.

26:57.991 --> 27:00.698
[ lndistinct conversations]

27:12.422 --> 27:14.378
No, thank you, Toby.

27:16.927 --> 27:18.167
Are you okay?

27:18.303 --> 27:21.295
My systems are operating
at full capacity.

27:21.431 --> 27:23.296
l was actually hoping you could
help me with something.

27:23.433 --> 27:24.718
Mm.

27:24.852 --> 27:28.640
I took one look at the maths
homework, and it is impossible.

27:28.772 --> 27:31.889
The task can be completed
once you know the formula.

27:32.025 --> 27:33.640
Right.

27:33.777 --> 27:34.937
And I know it would be cheating

27:35.070 --> 27:37.527
if I got a synth brain
to help me do the work.

27:37.656 --> 27:39.942
Only if I keep getting fails,
they're gonna put me

27:40.075 --> 27:42.111
-in a lower group --
-It is cheating

27:42.244 --> 27:45.532
to use a synth
to complete the assignment.

27:47.124 --> 27:50.036
But perhaps I can help you
work out the formula.

27:50.169 --> 27:51.158
Yeah?

27:51.295 --> 27:52.956
You can come to my house later
if you want.

27:53.630 --> 27:55.006
Okay.

28:03.098 --> 28:05.430
ASTRID: They said
you wanted to talk to me.

28:09.188 --> 28:11.224
I didn't choose
to get you involved in this.

28:11.356 --> 28:13.347
It's not my fault
if you've been hurt.

28:16.904 --> 28:19.941
You are very realistic,
you know?

28:20.490 --> 28:23.197
Right down to excuses.

28:27.122 --> 28:29.329
You lied to me.

28:30.375 --> 28:32.991
You can understand why.

28:34.087 --> 28:36.078
No, I can't.

28:36.632 --> 28:38.418
I don't lie -- ever.

28:38.550 --> 28:41.383
Are the things you choose
not to keep secret

28:41.511 --> 28:43.012
things that could
get you killed?

28:43.972 --> 28:45.257
No.

28:46.725 --> 28:49.683
Well, that must make being open
a lot easier.

28:50.437 --> 28:52.974
Why didn't you tell me?

28:53.857 --> 28:56.599
Because I didn't know
if I could trust you.

28:57.236 --> 28:59.568
That's bullshit.

29:02.366 --> 29:07.110
Because...you liked me,

29:07.246 --> 29:10.158
and I didn't want you
to stop.

29:20.092 --> 29:21.878
Well, I didn't.

29:26.431 --> 29:28.296
Even when you left.

29:30.686 --> 29:32.347
Even now.

29:41.071 --> 29:42.936
I could have loved you.

29:44.116 --> 29:45.856
I know.

29:51.248 --> 29:53.455
l have to go.

30:09.516 --> 30:11.757
They're not going to let her go.

30:11.893 --> 30:14.179
You do know that.

30:14.313 --> 30:17.430
Okay. Let's just say
that she can think.

30:17.566 --> 30:19.181
She can feel, in a way.

30:19.318 --> 30:21.650
She's an extraordinary machine,
an amazing creature.

30:21.778 --> 30:22.858
There's no doubt about that.

30:22.988 --> 30:25.730
But rights?

30:26.825 --> 30:28.361
A trial?

30:29.328 --> 30:31.193
It's never going to happen.

30:32.998 --> 30:36.490
They're out there --
the others like her,

30:36.626 --> 30:39.208
and we need to bring them in
quickly,

30:39.338 --> 30:41.624
into our moral universe.

30:41.757 --> 30:43.839
The burden of proof is on you,

30:43.967 --> 30:47.300
and I'm afraid you have
no hard evidence.

30:49.097 --> 30:51.429
Think about what I said.

31:00.067 --> 31:02.149
[Keys jingling]

31:05.364 --> 31:07.855
[Dog barking in distance]

31:08.825 --> 31:10.907
[Engine shuts off]

31:13.997 --> 31:15.032
PETE:
Connor?

31:21.088 --> 31:22.624
How'd you get my number?

31:23.256 --> 31:25.508
Contact.
You got the money?

31:26.343 --> 31:27.253
You got the Seraph?

31:27.386 --> 31:29.172
It's close by.

31:30.889 --> 31:33.722
Why the, uh, reduced price?

31:34.434 --> 31:36.174
Part used.

31:39.689 --> 31:40.895
What type is it?

31:41.858 --> 31:44.315
Standard domestic model.

31:44.444 --> 31:48.403
Caucasian, female,
5'10", brown hair.

31:48.532 --> 31:50.944
Walked out on its owners
this morning.

31:56.832 --> 31:58.493
Talk to him.

32:05.006 --> 32:07.258
[Grunting]

32:13.181 --> 32:14.512
[Cellphone rings]

32:14.641 --> 32:16.142
-KAREN: Pete?
-[ Pete grunting ]

32:16.268 --> 32:17.599
[ Up-tempo music plays]

32:17.727 --> 32:18.887
Pete?

32:23.191 --> 32:25.147
You all right?

32:25.277 --> 32:26.858
What have we got?

32:33.994 --> 32:37.657
Listen to me,
Inspector Drummond.

32:37.789 --> 32:40.030
You're out of your depth.
Do you understand?

32:40.167 --> 32:42.203
Gonna get yourself killed.

32:42.794 --> 32:44.125
All right?

32:45.297 --> 32:46.878
Back off.

32:52.762 --> 32:54.844
[ Exhales deeply]

32:56.308 --> 32:58.890
Mattie, I need your help
with something.

32:59.019 --> 33:00.680
Butter first, then Marmite.

33:00.812 --> 33:01.847
Yeah.
Very funny.

33:01.980 --> 33:05.222
I need to hack into my
old work's computer system.

33:05.358 --> 33:06.222
Okay.

33:06.359 --> 33:08.395
Gonna need a remote server...

33:08.528 --> 33:10.359
-Yeah.
-...a grappling hook, some rope,

33:10.489 --> 33:12.195
tranquilizer guns
for the guards,

33:12.324 --> 33:14.315
and some sort of ninja suit.

33:14.451 --> 33:16.032
I really need your help.

33:16.161 --> 33:17.822
Why do you want to hack
your work anyway?

33:17.954 --> 33:19.330
JOE: Found something odd
in my contract,

33:19.456 --> 33:21.868
and I want to know
why I was fired.

33:22.000 --> 33:24.286
Okay.
We could do a key-word search.

33:24.419 --> 33:27.877
"Joseph Hawkins,"
"big beardy idiot."

33:28.006 --> 33:30.497
Don't know if that will bring
any results.

33:31.593 --> 33:33.458
Okay.
Here we go.

33:33.595 --> 33:34.926
It's an e-mail chain.

33:35.055 --> 33:38.718
Staff redundancy list.
Oh, here's your name.

33:38.850 --> 33:40.181
Okay.

33:40.310 --> 33:41.800
"Put forward for approval."

33:41.937 --> 33:44.223
"Approval granted."

33:44.356 --> 33:46.267
This is basically
just a paper trail --

33:46.399 --> 33:48.139
the moment they decided
to make redundancies

33:48.276 --> 33:49.561
to the moment
you got shit-canned.

33:49.694 --> 33:52.606
JOE: What are these
e-mail addresses here?

33:52.739 --> 33:55.025
They're, uh,
synth communications --

33:55.158 --> 33:58.776
basic programs so synths
can send format e-mails.

33:59.704 --> 34:01.444
But...

34:01.581 --> 34:02.912
What?

34:03.041 --> 34:06.374
Well, synth e-mails are supposed
to copy in a human account,

34:06.503 --> 34:07.868
but they haven't CC'd anyone.

34:08.004 --> 34:09.915
It's just synths.

34:11.550 --> 34:13.461
The whole chain,
from the first e-mail

34:13.593 --> 34:16.300
to when they decided to let you
go, it's all just synth.

34:20.976 --> 34:23.888
PETE:
[ Breathing heavily]

34:25.272 --> 34:27.354
[Engine shuts off]

34:31.194 --> 34:32.479
Who did this?

34:32.612 --> 34:34.318
Seraphim deal.
They knew it was a setup.

34:34.447 --> 34:36.187
Jesus Christ, Pete.
You bloody idiot.

34:36.324 --> 34:37.700
I'm sorry.

34:37.826 --> 34:39.782
-|'m taking you to hospital.
-|'m fine.

34:39.911 --> 34:41.776
No, you're not.

34:41.913 --> 34:44.074
You were right, you know.

34:44.207 --> 34:47.370
Whatever Seraphim are,
they're not conscious synths.

34:47.502 --> 34:48.867
[ Grunts ]
Hold it.

34:49.004 --> 34:50.960
[Groans]

34:51.089 --> 34:53.250
[ Breathing heavily]

34:56.344 --> 34:59.051
[ lndistinct conversations]

35:03.602 --> 35:04.933
I wasn't fired by management.

35:05.061 --> 35:06.471
-Joe, look.
-|'ve seen the files.

35:06.605 --> 35:09.813
This isn't a redundancy package.
It's a gagging order.

35:09.941 --> 35:11.897
Look, there was a glitch.
I don't know the details.

35:12.027 --> 35:14.268
Only that there were
a few corporate decisions

35:14.404 --> 35:16.065
that were made
without the proper authority.

35:16.197 --> 35:17.186
We're trying to make it right!

35:17.324 --> 35:18.655
You're trying to keep it quiet.

35:18.783 --> 35:20.774
Joe, I'm saying this
as a friend now.

35:20.910 --> 35:23.322
Do yourself a favor.
Sign the form. Take the money.

35:23.455 --> 35:25.036
I know you need it!

35:25.165 --> 35:27.076
This is how we lose, you know.

35:27.208 --> 35:29.665
It won't be robots rising up
to slaughter us in our beds.

35:29.794 --> 35:31.750
It's machines
sending silent messages

35:31.880 --> 35:34.337
in the middle of the night
when no one else is looking.

35:35.675 --> 35:38.212
You're right. I need the money,
and l have to take it.

35:38.345 --> 35:40.336
| just came to tell you
what I think,

35:40.472 --> 35:42.838
'cause that's what people do.

35:47.854 --> 35:49.060
l have a reservation.

35:49.189 --> 35:51.225
Mr. Khoury is waiting for you.

35:51.358 --> 35:54.350
-May I take your coat, madam?
-Yes, please.

35:55.528 --> 35:57.564
Please follow me.

36:02.827 --> 36:04.567
Thank you.

36:06.873 --> 36:08.409
Athena.

36:08.541 --> 36:10.077
Hey.

36:18.593 --> 36:21.960
They tell me this --
this wine is good.

36:23.306 --> 36:25.763
I don't really know anything
about wine.

36:26.393 --> 36:28.634
I mean, it tastes nice.

36:29.270 --> 36:30.851
What do you think?

36:34.693 --> 36:36.433
Mm.

36:36.569 --> 36:37.979
It's okay.

36:39.114 --> 36:40.650
You a wine person?

36:40.782 --> 36:41.692
No.

36:41.825 --> 36:43.031
Mm.

36:43.159 --> 36:45.320
Well, it's expensive.

36:46.705 --> 36:49.617
Anyways, it's good to see you.

36:50.166 --> 36:51.906
You too.

36:52.043 --> 36:53.749
I ordered for us.

36:53.878 --> 36:55.379
I hope that's all right.

36:55.505 --> 36:57.712
Normally, I wouldn't do that,
but this place,

36:57.841 --> 37:00.048
they do something with
the sea bass that is just --

37:00.176 --> 37:02.963
It would break my heart if you
didn't get a chance to try it.

37:03.096 --> 37:04.256
That's fine.

37:04.389 --> 37:06.095
You a sea bass person?

37:06.725 --> 37:08.511
-[Laughs]
-I guess we'll find out.

37:17.986 --> 37:19.317
Odi?

37:22.407 --> 37:24.193
What are you doing?

37:25.785 --> 37:28.197
I need to get out, Mattie.

37:32.083 --> 37:34.460
And I don't think you're allowed
to keep me here.

37:35.712 --> 37:37.168
Do you know where you're going?

37:38.548 --> 37:40.209
-Yes.
-[ Latch clicks ]

37:41.342 --> 37:43.628
[Birds chirping]

38:05.116 --> 38:07.232
This was George's house.

38:08.661 --> 38:11.403
You didn't know him very well --
your father?

38:11.539 --> 38:13.450
No. He split from my mom
pretty early on.

38:13.583 --> 38:14.993
She raised you by herself?

38:15.627 --> 38:19.620
No. She mostly did heroin
by herself, actually.

38:20.173 --> 38:25.088
l was raised by the state,
in and out of the foster system

38:25.220 --> 38:28.257
till I landed on my parents
at 17.

38:29.015 --> 38:32.758
Their sons, uh, died --
muscular dystrophy.

38:32.894 --> 38:34.350
Takes your kids bit by bit,

38:34.479 --> 38:36.344
makes you watch
while it does it.

38:38.066 --> 38:40.352
You've never read a cover story
on me, have you?

38:40.485 --> 38:42.225
I care about your work,
not your private life.

38:42.362 --> 38:43.727
Mm.

38:43.863 --> 38:45.694
I got that vibe.

38:45.824 --> 38:47.735
It's one of the things I like
about you.

38:49.577 --> 38:50.407
Mm.

38:56.835 --> 38:58.575
Looks delicious.

39:03.049 --> 39:05.540
What shall we drink to?

39:05.677 --> 39:07.167
The sea bass.

39:08.388 --> 39:10.424
How about
consciousness transference?

39:14.936 --> 39:16.722
Cheers.

39:18.898 --> 39:20.434
You've been spying on me.

39:22.944 --> 39:24.684
We remotely track
the work stations

39:24.821 --> 39:26.231
of all our employees.

39:26.364 --> 39:27.649
And frankly, I'm concerned

39:27.782 --> 39:29.898
about your late-night
shopping decisions.

39:30.034 --> 39:31.740
It's not what I hired you to do.

39:31.870 --> 39:33.735
That is -- That is just --

39:33.872 --> 39:36.909
What, a gross intrusion
of your personal privacy?

39:37.667 --> 39:39.999
How do you think
| make my living?

39:42.964 --> 39:45.421
I'm just quietly mulling over

39:45.550 --> 39:47.336
whether or not
I should fire you.

39:48.469 --> 39:50.505
What do you think?

39:50.638 --> 39:53.380
I think it would be
a huge mistake.

39:53.516 --> 39:54.221
Why?

39:54.350 --> 39:58.889
Because I am about to crack
how to transfer consciousness

39:59.022 --> 39:59.932
into a machine.

40:00.064 --> 40:01.520
Human consciousness --
real consciousness.

40:01.649 --> 40:03.605
Yeah.

40:03.735 --> 40:04.850
Like an entire replication?

40:04.986 --> 40:06.351
You could just take
the essence of me

40:06.487 --> 40:07.567
and put it into a computer?

40:07.697 --> 40:09.733
I could put it into a body.

40:12.243 --> 40:15.485
You may not yet be able
to create a conscious synth

40:15.622 --> 40:17.283
out of nothing.

40:17.415 --> 40:19.406
But consciousness
transference --

40:19.542 --> 40:21.624
That is the next big leap
forward.

40:21.753 --> 40:22.833
And if I fire you?

40:23.671 --> 40:25.286
Someone else will hire me
to do it.

40:25.423 --> 40:28.005
And in the next 20 years,
Qualia will be mentioned

40:28.134 --> 40:31.171
in the same sentence
as LaserDiscs and Betamax.

40:31.304 --> 40:33.590
Well, why do I need you?

40:33.723 --> 40:35.930
l have all your research.

40:36.059 --> 40:38.801
I paid for it.
I own it.

40:39.354 --> 40:42.517
Everything on my servers
is mine.

40:44.275 --> 40:45.685
Everything.

40:50.239 --> 40:53.857
Well, let me help you
be the head of the company

40:53.993 --> 40:56.655
that figured out
how to cheat death.

40:57.705 --> 41:03.291
| just -- | just need more time
and the right synths.

41:03.920 --> 41:05.535
The right synths?

41:05.672 --> 41:06.878
David Elster's prototypes.

41:07.006 --> 41:10.464
He wrote the original
consciousness code for them.

41:11.886 --> 41:13.751
They are still alive.

41:13.888 --> 41:17.005
They are out there somewhere,
living in secret.

41:18.226 --> 41:20.012
How is that possible?

41:20.144 --> 41:23.762
Because Leo Elster
has been protecting them.

41:23.898 --> 41:25.013
David Elster's kid?

41:25.149 --> 41:26.480
Mm-hmm.

41:26.609 --> 41:27.769
He died.

41:29.529 --> 41:31.941
